{
  "stem": "14613.4",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We called it organizing, because stealing is something against our ethics.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So when somebody put it in quotation marks, 'stole' something, like bread, that was, we organized it.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I organized such a bread from a-- from away, and away from a bakery when they were carrying a lot of breads.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "This was really [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] something that I did out of desperation, because had I been caught, then I would immediately be killed or tortured.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And that's it.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So somehow--but we were so hungry after, I don't know, a few days or a week, that you just took measures that you normally shouldn't take.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And when I look back on it, and the unusual thing would happen that I did take the bread, and the Germans did not see it.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But I had a few thousand eyes that have seen it.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And these were also the inmates of this camp.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And the moment I took the bread and pulled out from the-- from the eyes of the Germans, a few thousand inmates of Auschwitz jumped on me.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we had a pile of people consisting of a few hundred people on top of me.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I am holding the bread, being on the bottom of the pile, so that when finally the Germans have seen what is going on-- a pile of people on top of another-- and they started to beat them, so that everybody dispersed.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I was on the bottom of the pile.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And all I had is maybe two crumbs of bread in my fist.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "That's what it was left.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] it's difficult for somebody who wasn't there to understand it.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
